[SN]TITLE[SN]
India's ancient university returns to life

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Nalanda, in northern India, was an eminent centre of higher education long before there were any students at Oxford, Cambridge or Europe's oldest university, Bologna.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
28 May 2013 Last updated at 17:01 BST
The ruins of the original college are now a popular tourist site - but there are plans to establish a modern day Nalanda University in one of India's poorest states.
The BBC's Rupa Jha reports.
